{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a44d7f7d-19a2-4483-930d-fe9fc050c6ec","content":"In **.NET 10 SDK**, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively** — no opt-in required. You can remove the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property since it's now the default behavior.\n\nYour simplified `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is **no longer needed** with .NET 10 SDK — MTP is the default test orchestration.\n- Keep `EnableMSTestRunner` — it builds your test project as an executable using MTP.\n- `dotnet test` will invoke the MTP-based runner directly without the VSTest adapter layer.\n\nWant me to update your project file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9a4284df-d23c-4e74-ac91-0292d289b266","outputTokens":281,"requestId":"E3E0:164582:16EB7F7:198B851:6A052095"},"id":"62f38725-2aba-45e4-9560-36b28a19643d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:08:44.442Z","parentId":"487f7f33-756c-4c82-ab74-a6182f2dcad2"}
